cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY 

The paper discusses an information retrieval tool for large-scale bibliographic databases and applies it to a dataset in astronomy and astrophysics. This suggests a focus on information retrieval and data analysis, which aligns with the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses clustering algorithms and their application to delineating topics, which aligns with the sub-categories of Computation and Language (cs.CL) and Computers and Society (cs.CY).
